            <h2 class="card-title">Living in a Big City</h2>
            <div class="carousel-container">
                <div class="carousel-track" data-track="4">
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label">INTRODUCTION</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">There is a huge concern that</span> urban migration continues to accelerate globally. <span class="key-expression">It is common knowledge that</span> cities offer abundant opportunities, <span class="key-expression">however/nevertheless</span> they also present unique challenges. <span class="key-expression">Therefore, we should find ways in which we can address/deal with/tackle this problem/issue</span> of urbanization.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label for">ARGUMENTS FOR</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The main advantage of</span> city living <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it provides access to superior career opportunities and higher salaries. <span class="key-expression">For example</span>, major corporations and innovative startups concentrate in urban centers.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">One positive aspect of</span> urban environments <span class="key-expression">is that</span> they offer extensive cultural amenities. <span class="key-expression">In particular</span>, residents enjoy museums, theaters, diverse restaurants, and vibrant entertainment options.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">It is also worth noting that</span> cities typically have better public transportation and healthcare facilities, <span class="key-expression">hence</span> improving quality of life.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label against">ARGUMENTS AGAINST</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The argument against</span> urban living <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it involves exorbitant living costs. <span class="key-expression">This is largely due to/owing to</span> high demand for limited housing in desirable locations.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The obvious drawback of</span> big cities <span class="key-expression">is that</span> they suffer from pollution, noise, and overcrowding. <span class="key-expression">That is to say</span>, the fast-paced lifestyle can negatively impact mental and physical health.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">One clear solution would be</span> to develop sustainable urban planning initiatives, <span class="key-expression">although/even though</span> this requires substantial investment and political will.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label">CONCLUSION</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">All things considered, to sum up</span>, city life presents a complex mix of opportunities and challenges. <span class="key-expression">It is clear that, despite some of the arguments</span>, urban centers will continue to attract people seeking professional advancement and cultural diversity.</p>
