        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-number">5</div>
            <h2 class="card-title">Learning English</h2>
            <div class="carousel-container">
                <div class="carousel-track" data-track="5">
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label">INTRODUCTION</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">It has always played a significant role in our lives</span> to communicate across cultures. <span class="key-expression">Recent studies show that</span> English has become the global lingua franca, <span class="key-expression">despite/in spite of</span> debates about linguistic diversity. <span class="key-expression">Hence, it is imperative to discuss the causes/the impact of</span> learning English as a second language.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label for">ARGUMENTS FOR</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The main advantage of</span> learning English <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it opens doors to international career opportunities. <span class="key-expression">For example</span>, multinational companies require English proficiency for most professional positions.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">One positive aspect of</span> English fluency <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it grants access to vast educational resources. <span class="key-expression">In particular</span>, most academic research and online courses are published in English.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">It is also worth noting that</span> English facilitates international travel and cultural exchange, <span class="key-expression">hence</span> enhancing global understanding.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label against">ARGUMENTS AGAINST</span>
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The argument against</span> prioritizing English <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it may threaten linguistic diversity. <span class="key-expression">This is largely due to/owing to</span> the diminishing use of minority languages.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">The obvious drawback of</span> English dominance <span class="key-expression">is that</span> it can create educational inequality. <span class="key-expression">For instance</span>, students without access to quality English instruction face limited opportunities.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="section">
                            <p class="section-text"><span class="key-expression">By far the best way to tackle</span> this challenge <span class="key-expression">is</span> to promote multilingualism while recognizing English's practical importance, <span class="key-expression">although/even though</span> balancing both remains difficult.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="carousel-slide">
                        <div class="section">
                            <span class="section-label">CONCLUSION</span>
